title: For Sale:  Pre WWI Model 1903 Springfield 30.06 Rifle
location: Cary, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
1908 production, serial number 325xxx.  The metal and stock are in very good condition. The barrel is almost new reading less than .001 of wear on my muzzle gauge. Shoots great and is very accurate.  August, 1944 barrel date, so it went back through the arsenal at that time and was used during WWII as well as WWI.  High number bolt.  RA-P arsenal stamp which I believe was the Raritan Arsenal.  I have 3 of these and am running out of space, so this is up for sale.

This is an early number receiver and users are cautioned not to shoot them as they were only single heat treated and a very small number of them cracked during use.  They were taken out of service after WWI and many, this one included were put back into service during WWII.  If I recall my research correctly, there is no record of one of these receivers having cracked in use since about 1928.  Shooting it is, of course, at your own risk.  The rifle was used during WWII without a problem, and I have shot it many times, so, for me at least, the rifle is fine to shoot.  If you don't want to shoot it, the rifle is a great collector's piece.  

I might consider interesting trades.
